author: Inside Edition
description: Deanna Lamonia recorded every moment of a terrifying mall shooting in San Jose, California. There was chaos as families enjoying Black Friday suddenly heard shots ring out. Despite this isolated act of chaos, Black Friday turned into a triumph for American businesses. Shoppers spent a record $11.8 billion in-store and online, a 9.1 percent increase over last year. The shopping spree continued with Cyber Monday. Inside Edition got a first hand look at the most popular items this year.
title: Video Shows Chaos During Black Friday Shooting At California Mall

author: Inside Edition
description: In October during a physical, President Donald Trump underwent an MRI. The White House has never revealed what part of Trump's body was scanned and the president claimed he didn't know either. The pressure to release the results came after the president attacked Minnesota's governor, calling him the "R" word. Minnesota Governor Tim Walz fired back, demanding Trump come clean about his health. White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt revealed the MRI was focused on his heart and abdomen.
title: Reason Why President Donald Trump Underwent MRI Revealed

author: Inside Edition
description: Luigi Mangione appeared in court Monday as a crucial pre-trial hearing went underway. Prosecutors played the surveillance video showing the assassination of United Health Care CEO Brian Thompson outside the Hilton Hotel in Manhattan. Thursday marks the first anniversary of the murder. The defense is asking that the contents of Mangione's backpack, found when he was arrested at a McDonald's in Pennsylvania, to be excluded from the trial.
title: Accused Assassin Luigi Mangione Appears Back in Court

author: Inside Edition
description: In the first episode of the new "Stranger Things" season, there is a missing person for Jane Hopper, Millie Bobby Brown's character, also known as Eleven. The poster includes a phone number with an Indiana area code, and it actually works. Inside Edition dialed the number from Jane Hopper, aka Eleven's, missing poster in the show. On the other end of the call was a recording from the show's police department in the fictional town of Hawkins, Indiana.
title: Phone Number Shown In 'Stranger Things' Episode Actually Works

author: Inside Edition
description: Some customers are complaining that rental car agencies like Hertz are using new AI vehicle scanning technology to charge fees for tiny dings and dents. INSIDE EDITION spoke with two Hertz customers who say they were charged when Hertz scanners detected small dents in their rental cars upon return. Hertz says the scanners “bring precision and transparency to a historically inconsistent process,” and “We try to get it right for every customer and, when we fall short, we make it right.”
title: Hertz Installs AI Scanners to Check Drivers’ Cars for Damage

author: Inside Edition
description: Four members of one family left Clearwater, Florida, on board a 25-foot catamaran to celebrate Dennis Woods’ 70th birthday. Disaster struck when the boat flipped upside down. A GoFundMe has been set up to rescue the boat; for more information, click this link: https://bit.ly/4pCnbQj
title: Family Was Stranded For Hours After Boat Capsized #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Two guests at a four-star restaurant in Virginia asked to see inside the eatery's wine cellar. The owner says while the woman distracted him with questions, her accomplice allegedly slipped six bottles of wine worth $38,000 under his coat.
title: Diners Dash With $38,000 Worth Of Wine #shorts
